[{"id":706,"date":"2026-04-26T15:12:03","date_gmt":"2026-04-26T15:12:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/cms.edrishusein.com\/?post_type=project&#038;p=706"},"modified":"2026-06-16T16:11:26","modified_gmt":"2026-06-16T16:11:26","slug":"work-os-wordpress-plugin","status":"publish","type":"project","link":"https:\/\/cms.edrishusein.com\/projects\/work-os-wordpress-plugin\/","title":{"rendered":"Work OS WordPress Plugin"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A WordPress plugin for managing a freelance career from wp-admin, integrating AI-powered research, proposals, and GitHub portfolio sync.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"featured_media":707,"menu_order":4,"template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-706","project","type-project","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"acf_fields":{"project_content":{"challenge":"<p>Freelancers working from WordPress need a unified place to research prospective clients, draft proposals, track outcomes, store documents, and keep their portfolio in sync with their GitHub activity. Without tooling, these tasks are spread across separate apps and manual workflows. This plugin consolidates all of that into a single wp-admin interface.<\/p>\n","solution":"<p>Work OS is built as a PHP WordPress plugin that creates four custom database tables and a set of admin screens for each workflow area. It integrates Anthropic Claude Sonnet for proposal drafting, fit analysis, and blog generation, and Google Gemini 2.5 Flash with Search grounding for company research. GitHub Sync compares public repos against a custom post type for portfolio projects, reads actual README content via the GitHub API, and uses Claude to populate ACF fields on generated draft CPT entries. All API calls are manually triggered; no background processing runs automatically.<\/p>\n"},"project_links":{"live_site":"","github":"https:\/\/github.com\/Husein-Edris\/work-os"},"project_overview":